reviewText: Zombies vs. Strippers isn't the best entry in the whole versus series of zombies. But, surprisingly enough, I was entertained by it. The pacing is good and there are actually some funny moments in it. And the strippers aren't that bad either.

reviewText: Zombies vs. Strippers is the latest funfest from Full Moon Studios, responsible for the Gingerdead Man, Evil Bong, and Puppet Master series'. It's a kick-butt horror-action-comedy that is fast-paced and fun with great characters and some humorous dialogue. It was almost as good as Zombie Strippers. The only thing it was missing was Robert England and Jenna Jameson. Also, there is a good bit of nudity in this movie. Three women appear topless. Zombies vs. Strippers is just a great zombie movie, possibly the best since Zombieland. And no I did not work on this movie, which I'm sure some people will accuse me of since I gave a 5 star review to a movie called Zombies vs. Strippers. I just love fun B-movies!
summary: Almost As Good As Zombie Strippers!

reviewText: I think if there is a complaint for this film it has to be, "It's a movie that didn't know what it wanted to be".  It is not a bad film, fairly average Full Moon styling.  The characters are decent and so is the acting.  The effects are also good.  Typical day at the office offering, but the movie didn't know if it wanted to be serious, scary, high action OR funny.  There are comical elements, as well as some pretty serious tone.  Mild action, mild dialogue - nothing bad, just you never got a feeling like it was trying to be scary or funny, just somewhere in between.  I think if they found the courage to pick a certain route, the movie could have been more than it is.  They played it safe.  You have blood, gore, nudity, zombies and action; it is all there in fairly equal amounts.This is a pretty good movie, worthy to watch or even buy.  It just didn't thrill you like it could have.
summary: Middle of the road rating for middle of the road movie

reviewText: This movie has a lot of the old style gore with basic body props and no CGI effects. Not to say, I like CGI, no I don't care either way. And, I do admire the old use of props instead. So, if you like that style of filming than you should watch it.The zombies yell out brains a lot. There's the basic idea of being bite by a zombie will make you turn in this movie. There are a lot of slap stick humor in this one. I didn't really like the fact that every character seemed too stupid for their own good. It felt like they were all going to die because of their stupidity, and not really because of the horde of zombies. They really could had lived if they were smarter, but, I guess, that's a B movies for you. lolI also thought the strippers would be much prettier and sexier too, but they aren't. Most were pretty ugly to call themselves strippers. I give this movie 2 stars and it would had got 3 stars, if they had better looking girls.Brains!!!!!!!!Oops, I mean.Better...girls!!!

reviewText: The title pretty much says it all. There is of course the irony of people going to a strip club to look for brains.Topless Jasmine about to perform oral: "What do you like most about me?"Zombie Marvin: "Brains."During the zombie outbreak the club has suspended its rules about touching the dancers. Bambi (Victoria Levine) spends most of the film minus her top. The film contains humor, but lacks true horror.Watch it for the girls. reviewerName: William D. Colburn "buys things on amazon far...
reviewText: The people in this movie can act.  It's like they thought they were in a real movie!  The problem is, the movie itself tries too hard to a serious movie as well.With the title and subject matter, I don't want to see a serious movie.  I want funny and stupid.  There is just a little too much serious here and while they do try for funny and stupid the serious kind of ruins it.Not a bad movie, but not really a good movie either.I don't regret buying it.UPDATE!I wrote the part above while I was still watching the movie.  I had yet to see a stripper with a high-heel duct taped to a stick fight Michael Jackson from Thriller.It's still not a great movie, but it has moments.  I still don't regret buying it.
